          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2623670-peggy?shelf=canadian">canadian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2623670-peggy?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer392424316" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16000129774300936184">I really liked this book. It is quite unusual, featuring both an exotic setting [Guatemala and later northern Labrador] and a familiar one [Toronto] with the titular character who is mute, because of past trauma, perhaps exacerbated by mental illness. It&apos;s a mystery, but a whydunnit, rather than a whodunnit. Jerry Simpson is a psychoanalyst who is murdered (not a spoiler, it&apos;s the first line of chapter 2) by the young woman he has rescued from the box. The book is mostly told from the point of v</span>
  <span id="freeText16000129774300936184" style="display:none">I really liked this book. It is quite unusual, featuring both an exotic setting [Guatemala and later northern Labrador] and a familiar one [Toronto] with the titular character who is mute, because of past trauma, perhaps exacerbated by mental illness. It's a mystery, but a whydunnit, rather than a whodunnit. Jerry Simpson is a psychoanalyst who is murdered (not a spoiler, it's the first line of chapter 2) by the young woman he has rescued from the box. The book is mostly told from the point of view of his girlfriend, who struggles to understand why it happened.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16000129774300936184" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

